<div class="output_markdown rendered_html output_subarea ">
<p>Begin with a simple triangle defined as line segments.</p>

<pre><code>lines = [
    [-1, 0, 0, 1],
    [0, 1, 1, 0],
    [1, -1, 0, 0],
]
SIZE = len(lines)</code></pre>

</div>


<div class="output_markdown rendered_html output_subarea ">

<pre><code>__nodes__ = lambda lines: (lines[0][0::2], lines[1][0::2], lines[2][0::2])

</code></pre>
<p><strong>nodes</strong> are the corners of the triangles, for example:</p>

<pre><code>A, B, C = __nodes__(lines)
o and print(A, B, C)

</code></pre>
<hr>

</div>

---
[-1, 0] [0, 1] [1, 0]

---


<div class="output_markdown rendered_html output_subarea ">
<p>For a triangle, we derive it children <strong>triangles</strong> for the <strong>nodes</strong> of the <em>lines</em>.</p>

<pre><code>def __triangles__(lines):
    A, B, C = __nodes__(lines)
    X = (A[0]+B[0])/2, (A[1]+B[1])/2
    Y = (B[0]+C[0])/2, (B[1]+C[1])/2
    Z = (C[0]+A[0])/2, (C[1]+A[1])/2
    return [[_0[0], _1[0], _0[1], _1[1]] for _ in [
        [[A, X], [X, Z], [Z, A]], [[B, Y], [Y, X], [X, B]], [[C, Z], [Z, Y], [Y, C]],
    ] for _0, _1 in _]

</code></pre>
<hr>
<p>Consider the <code>text</code> diagram below for reference to the node positions.</p>
<p><code>
  B
 X Y
A Z C
</code></p>
<hr>

</div>


<div class="output_markdown rendered_html output_subarea ">
<p>Recursively <strong>generate</strong> the Sierpinsi triangles.</p>

<pre><code>#     def __generate__(levels=4):
levels=8
triangles = [lines]
for LEVEL in range(levels):
    for _ in range(0, len(triangles[-1]), 3):
        _ is 0 and triangles.append([]) or triangles[-1].extend(
            __triangles__(triangles[-2][_:_+3]))</code></pre>

</div>


<div class="output_markdown rendered_html output_subarea ">
<p>Create the Bokeh ColumnDataSource from the <code>assert triangles</code></p>

<pre><code>source = pd.concat({
    _: pd.DataFrame(__, columns=['x0', 'x1', 'y0', 'y1']) for _, __ in enumerate(triangles)
}).reset_index(-1, drop=True).pipe(plotting.ColumnDataSource)</code></pre>

</div>


<div class="output_markdown rendered_html output_subarea ">
<p><code>from bokeh.models import CustomJSTransform</code> to add some color flare.</p>

<pre><code>p = plotting.figure(webgl=True, height=600, width=800)
p.segment(
    *(((_+str(__)for __ in range(2) for _ in 'xy' ))), 
    source=source, line_width=8, line_alpha=.3, line_color={
        'field': 'x0', 
        'transform': CustomJSTransform(
            v_func="""return [].slice.call(xs).map(function(_,i){return ['red', 'green', 'blue'][i%3]})"""),}
) and plotting.show(p)</code></pre>
